# "Put website down" = stop the Staff Hub web stack

When the user says **"put website down"**, **"website down"**, **"take the site down"**, or similar — **execute the shutdown immediately**. Do not only explain how; run the commands.

## What to stop

The live site is `staff_hub_serve.py` (supervisor) + Flask (`web_api.py` on `:5000`) + `cloudflared` tunnel. Stopping Flask alone is not enough — kill the full stack.

## How (PowerShell, repo root)

```powershell
$bot = 'C:\Users\kiere\Desktop\Wave Management Bot'
Get-CimInstance Win32_Process -Filter "Name='python.exe'" |
    Where-Object { $_.CommandLine -match 'staff_hub_serve\.py|web_api\.py' } |
    ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.ProcessId -Force }
Stop-Process -Name cloudflared -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
Get-Process wscript -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force
```

## Verify it's down

- `http://localhost:5000/ping` should fail / refuse connection
- Report result to the user

## Opposite command

**"put website up"** / **"bring the site back"** → run `restart_staff_hub.ps1` from repo root.
